      <title><![CDATA[Ep.3 Bill Macnaught — a librarian’s life]]></title>
      <link>https://natlib.govt.nz/blog/posts/ep-3-bill-macnaught-a-librarians-life</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<i>The Library Loudhailer talks to retiring National Librarian Bill Macnaught about being a librarian, his long career working with libraries and his time at the National Library.</i>
      
      <p>Listen to Bill Macnaught talk about the controversial Angel of the North, Puke Ariki, the value of reading and many other highlights of his career.</p>
      <h3>Mentioned in this podcast</h3>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/he-tohu">He Tohu</a> — Exhbition of three founding documents of New Zealand, 1835 He Whakaputanga, 1840 Treaty of Waitangi and 1893 Women's Suffrage Petition. </li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://www.tepunafoundation.org.nz/">Te Puna Foundation</a> — Te Puna Foundation is the fundraising body for the National Library of New Zealand.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/about-us/collaborative-projects/new-zealand-libraries-partnership-programme">New Zealand libraries partnership programme</a> — COVID-19 recovery work being led by the National Library to support librarians and library services across New Zealand.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/librarians/apnk">Aotearoa People’s Network Kaharoa (APNK)</a> — living, learning, creating in the digital world.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/librarians/kotui">Kōtui</a> — is a shared service that provides New Zealand public libraries with an affordable, efficient option to help them manage their collections.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/about-us/collaborative-projects/new-zealand-reading-ambassador">Te Awhi Rito New Zealand Reading Ambassador</a> — As a national reading role model to  help create a nation of readers.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/records/40685086">‘Funiculi Funicula’</a> — podcast intro theme song. The final track on from Keil Isles album ‘Take Off’.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/collections/a-z/archive-of-new-zealand-music">Archive of New Zealand Music</a> — the Archive of New Zealand Music is the world's largest archive of unpublished material relating to New Zealand music and musicians</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/records/38215350">‘The sailor's hornpipe’</a> — performed by Pipe-Major James Patterson. Podcast outro music. </li>
      </ul>
      <p><i>A transcript of this episode is available at <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/blog/posts/ep-3-bill-macnaught-a-librarians-life">https://natlib.govt.nz/blog/posts/ep-3-bill-macnaught-a-librarians-life</a>.</i></p>]]></description>
