      <title><![CDATA[Ep.5 Ulu Afaese — on loving libraries]]></title>
      <link>https://natlib.govt.nz/blog/posts/ep-5-ulu-afaese-on-loving-libraries</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<i>Ulu Afaese tells us about his journey into the library world, studying librarianship and working in libraries.</i>
     
      <p>Ulu Afaese is as a Content Analyst for digitalpasifik.org and has worked in various libraries including as a librarian in the Alexander Turnbull Library. He talks about how he found himself working in libraries.</p>
      <h3>Mentioned in the podcast</h3>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://digitalpasifik.org/">www.digitalpasifik.org</a> — digitalpasifik.org aims to empower people in and of the Pacific Islands, enabling them to see, discover and explore items of digitised cultural heritage that are held in collections around the world.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/about-us/collaborative-projects/pacific-virtual-museum">Pacific Virtual Museum project</a> — the project team that runs digitalpasifik.org. The Pilot Program is an Australian Government initiative managed by the Office of the Pacific in Australia’s Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade (DFAT). It will be implemented by Te Puna Mātauranga o Aotearoa, the National Library of New Zealand, in collaboration with the National Library of Australia.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
      <li>
      <a href="https://tiaki.natlib.govt.nz/#details=ecatalogue.466589"> Papers relating to Samoa: John C, Klein active 1870-1890</a> — Link to Alexander Turnbull catalogue.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Related content</h3>

      <p><a href="https://digitalpasifik.org/blog/samoan-language-week-a-reflection">Samoan Language Week: A reflection</a> — Blog by Ulu Afaese about Samoan Language week. </p>
      <p><a href="https://digitalpasifik.org/blog/bridges-between-worlds">Bridges between worlds</a> — Blog about ‘contribute your story’ function on digitalpasifik.org.  </p>
      <p><a href="https://digitalpasifik.org/blog/authority-representation-and-reality">Authority, Representation and Reality</a> — Blog about how the thinking behind the ‘contribute your story’ function on digitalpasifik.org</p>
      <p><i>A transcript of this episode is available at <a href="https://natlib.govt.nz/blog/posts/ep-5-ulu-afaese-on-loving-libraries">https://natlib.govt.nz/blog/posts/ep-5-ulu-afaese-on-loving-libraries</a>.</i></p>]]></description>
